      • getLicenseValidityPeriod

        public int getLicenseValidityPeriod()
        Get license validity period in number of days. License expires after defined number of days passed over generation date. So, expiration date is generation date + validity period
        Returns:
        licenseValidProductEdition

      • setLicenseValidityPeriod

        public void setLicenseValidityPeriod(int licenseValidityPeriod)
        Set license validity period in number of days. License expires after defined number of days passed over generation date. So, expiration date is generation date + validity period. e.g. If you want to generate 1 year valid license, set validity period to 365 days.
        Parameters:
        licenseValidityPeriod -

      • getLicenseMaintenancePeriod

        public int getLicenseMaintenancePeriod()
        Get license maintenence validity period in number of days. License maintenance expires after defined number of days passed over generation date. So, maintenance expiration date is generation date + maintenance period
        Returns:
        licenseValidProductEdition

      • setLicenseMaintenancePeriod

        public void setLicenseMaintenancePeriod(int licenseMaintenancePeriod)
        Set license maintenance validity period in number of days. License maintenance expires after defined number of days passed over generation date. So, maintenance expiration date is generation date + maintenance period. e.g. If you want to generate 1 year maintenance valid license, set maintenance period to 365 days.

        licenseMaintenancePeriod -

      • getActivationReturnType

        public int getActivationReturnType()
        Return activation return type. There are two types of activation return type. The first one is activation code, it is a secure license key. The second one is license text. Integer values are 1 for activation code, and 2 for license text.
        Returns:
        activationReturnType

      • setActivationReturnType

        public void setActivationReturnType(int activationReturnType)
        Set activation return type. There are two types of activation return type. The first one is activation code, it is a secure license key. The second one is license text. Integer values are 1 for activation code, and 2 for license text.
        Parameters:
        activationReturnType -

      • getActivationHardwareIDSelection

        public int getActivationHardwareIDSelection()
        Get activation hardware ID selection value. It is an integer, and 1 for hardware ID from hostname; 2 for hardware ID from ethernet address; 3 for hardware ID from disk volume uuid; 4 for hardware ID from HDD serial number. A combination is used, and if && operand is used number is positive like 12, 13, 1234. If || operand is used number must be negative like -12, -13, -1234.
        Returns:
        activationHardwareIDSelection

      • setActivationHardwareIDSelection

        public void setActivationHardwareIDSelection(int activationHardwareIDSelection)
        Set activation hardware ID selection value. It is an integer, and 1 for hardware ID from hostname; 2 for hardware ID from ethernet address; 3 for hardware ID from disk volume uuid; 4 for hardware ID from HDD serial number. A combination is used, and if && operand is used number is positive like 12, 13, 1234. If || operand is used number must be negative like -12, -13, -1234.
        Parameters:
        activationHardwareIDSelection -
